 </title><link>https://faq.i3wm.org/question/879/is-posible-to-minimize-a-window/?answer=892#post-id-892</link><description>If I got you right, you don't wish to select other containers inside of tabbed (or stacked) layout when moving to the adjacent container. 

In version 4.4 there's an option called `force_focus_wrapping`. See [documentation](http://i3wm.org/docs/userguide.html#_focus_wrapping). I older versions, you are able to get around this by focusing parent container and then focusing adjacent.</description><pubDate>Wed, 12 Dec 2012 09:39:44 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://faq.i3wm.org/question/879/is-posible-to-minimize-a-window/?answer=892#post-id-892</guid></item><item><title>Answer by Michael for &lt;p&gt;i would like to minimize a window so it don't 'wake up' when i move btw windows with $mod+Right and $mod+Left.&lt;/p&gt;

